kernel_variant.question:
Let w : \mathbb{Z}^3 \to  \mathbb{Z} be the convolution kernel whose non-zero values are  

* w(0,0,0)=48;  

* w(\pm 1,0,0)=w(0,\pm 1,0)=w(0,0,\pm 1)=-13;  

* w(\pm 2,0,0)=w(0,\pm 2,0)=w(0,0,\pm 2)= 1;  

* w(\pm 1,\pm 1,0)=w(\pm 1,0,\pm 1)=w(0,\pm 1,\pm 1)= 2  

(the sign choices are independent in every occurrence); for all other lattice points set w=0.  
For a finite set S\subset \mathbb{Z}^3 put  

A(S)=\sum _{(s,s')\in S\times S} w(s-s').

Prove that A(S)>0 for every non-empty finite subset S of \mathbb{Z}^3.

